         <p id="PAZWXu" outputclass="Normal">** SCOs hold equivalent regulatory authority; this does not diminish or remove positional authority within the organization.</p>
         <p id="IqZOWQ" outputclass="Normal">The deputy or technical director to a SCO may exercise any SCO authority unless restricted in the FAR, as supplemented (e.g., individual authorized to execute a specific authority must be of a certain minimum grade/rank), or as specifically limited by the SCO. See <xref format="pdf" href="https://static.e-publishing.af.mil/production/1/saf_aq/publication/afi64-105/afi64-105.pdf" scope="external">
               <u>AFI 64-105</u>
            </xref> Contingency Contracting Support, to identify SCOs for contingency operations.</p>
         <p id="PnzltJ" outputclass="Normal">
